# Riftbound Sigils — Cursor Rules (v3 FINAL)

## Single Source of Truth

`docs/MASTER_GAME_BRIEF_v3_FINAL.md` governs every decision in this project.
This rules file is a summary and an enforcement layer. When they conflict, the brief wins.
Read the brief before starting any code generation task in this session.

---

## What This Game Is

A **landscape-orientation, side-view, formation-based auto-battler RPG** for mobile.

- Canvas: **844 × 390 px**, landscape only
- Heroes on the **LEFT** half. Enemies on the **RIGHT** half.
- HUD strip at the **BOTTOM** (80 px)
- Players configure their formation before battle
- Combat resolves **automatically** — no player input controls unit movement
- The player's only combat input during battle is **tapping a portrait button to fire an ultimate**

---

## Hard Prohibitions — Never Implement These

Each item below is a hard stop. If a prompt asks for one of these, refuse and explain which rule is violated.

### Portrait Orientation
Never use a canvas height greater than its width.
Never set Phaser width to 390 and height to 844.
The game is 844 × 390. Always.

### Drag-to-Move Controls
Never add touch drag handlers that move hero units during battle.
Never implement `pointerdown` / `pointermove` / `pointerup` sequences that reposition heroes.
Never implement `targetX` / `targetY` that a player sets by dragging.
Formation is set before battle on the FormationScene. Once battle starts, heroes move only under AI control.

### Manual Dodge Mechanics
Never implement player-controlled evasion, i-frames triggered by player input, or movement the player uses to avoid enemy attacks.
The player cannot dodge anything. The formation and class AI handle positioning.

### Roguelite Draft-Card Combat
Never implement a between-wave card selection screen.
Never implement a pool of augments shown to the player after a wave clears.
Never implement run-specific power upgrades chosen by the player during combat.
The roguelite draft loop is not part of this game.

