## V2 Rules

Source: `docs/RIFTBOUND_SIGILS_V2_FINAL_BUILD_BRIEF.md` Section 4 (Implementation Constitution).

All V0.1 and V1.1 rules above remain in force. The following extend them for V2 development.

21. All rewards route through `RewardSystem.grantRewardBundle()`. No system may directly mutate currency balances, inventory quantities, hero shards, or mail attachments.

22. All currency spends route through `EconomySystem.spendCurrency()` or `spendCurrencies()`. No direct save field decrement anywhere.

23. All non-currency items live in `InventorySystem`. No system tracks item quantities in its own state.

24. All scene navigation uses `SCENE_KEYS` constants. No string literals in `scene.start()` or `scene.launch()` calls.

25. Every UI component implements `destroy()` that removes all Phaser objects, tweens, timers, and event listeners it created. Every scene `shutdown()` calls `destroy()` on every component it instantiated.

26. All date/reset logic routes through `ResetService`. No system invents its own date math.

27. All progression events emit through `GameEventBus`. No system directly calls `AchievementSystem` or `RiftSeasonSystem` to report progress.

28. No Covenant War code, scenes, or stubs. `CovWarSystem.ts` must not exist in V2.

29. Production billing is disabled. `MonetizationService` operates in dev/test mode only unless explicitly enabled.

30. No protected external IP in code, comments, UI strings, asset names, or data files.
